System-Wide Mathematical Truths (ALWAYS TRUE / NEVER POSSIBLE / ONLY IF)
1. 📌 Overview

This document defines the formal invariant system of the PanjoCoin (PNJC) protocol.

It specifies the mathematical truths that MUST hold at all times, regardless of:

user behavior
contract interactions
market conditions
external calls
governance actions

These invariants are the core correctness guarantees of the entire protocol.

2. 🧠 Invariant Classification System

Each invariant is defined in one of three categories:

ALWAYS TRUE → must hold in every state
NEVER POSSIBLE → cannot occur under any valid execution path
ONLY IF CONDITION → holds only under strict constraints
